Quang Nguyen is an Intern Java Backend Developer with 0 years of commercial experience, primarily gaining practical skills through academic and personal projects. Their core expertise lies in developing robust backend services and RESTful APIs, implementing secure authentication using JWT, and integrating online payment solutions. They possess strong Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) skills and have experience building full-stack applications. Key projects include a Real Estate Web platform featuring property listings, contract management, and VNPay payment integration, and a Spring E-commerce Web application with comprehensive product management, search, filtering, shopping cart functionality, and secure checkout processes. These projects demonstrate proficiency in backend development with Spring Boot, Spring Security, Spring Data JPA, Hibernate, and MySQL, alongside frontend development using ReactJS and Redux Toolkit.
Technically, Quang is proficient in programming languages such as Java, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, and SQL. They possess hands-on experience with a comprehensive set of frameworks and libraries including Spring Boot, Spring MVC, Spring Security, Spring Data JPA, Hibernate, JQuery, Bootstrap, Thymeleaf, ReactJS, Redux Toolkit, JUnit, and Mockito for robust testing. Their database expertise includes MySQL and SQL Server. For DevOps and cloud services, they have practical exposure to Docker, AWS S3, and Firebase. They are adept with development tools such as Git, GitHub, Maven, and Postman, applying these in projects involving RESTful API development, JWT-based authentication, and payment integration.